2.title: Black Dahlia/Boston's Haunted Underworld

episode of.title: Haunted Encounters: Face to Face (TV Series 2012– )

2.plot: The Paranormal Syndicate first heads to Los Angeles, where they will investigate an ominous residence, believed to be the site of the infamous Black Dahlia murder. With the help of their canine investigator, Captain, will the team make contact with the killer himself? Then, the Syndicate heads to Boston, MA, where they gain exclusive access into a system of long-abandoned subway tunnels deep beneath the city. Serving as the epicenter to tragedies and death for over a century, will these unexplored tunnels be a hotbed of paranormal activity?

3.title: Eastern State Penitentiary

episode of.title: Haunted Encounters: Face to Face (TV Series 2012– )

3.plot: In this special episode, the Paranormal Syndicate gains unprecedented access into one of the world's most infamous "super haunts", The Eastern State Penitentiary. From torture, murder, suicide and sickness, thousands of violent criminals lost their lives behind the walls of this historic prison, and it is believed that many of their restless souls will be imprisoned here for eternity. Will they be able to handle this labyrinth of terror and walk away with documented proof of paranormal activity?

4.title: The Hotel Cecil/Kriescher Mansion

episode of.title: Haunted Encounters: Face to Face (TV Series 2012– )

4.plot: The Paranormal Syndicate heads to downtown Los Angeles to investigate the Hotel Cecil, which played host to several murders, rapes, and suicides and served as a hideout for two of history's most notorious serial killers. With the help of their canine investigator, Captain, can the team collect evidence of paranormal activity from the deceased guests who never checked out? 5.plot: The Paranormal Syndicate heads to North Adams, MA to investigate a mysterious Masonic temple, better known to most as the Houghton Mansion.
